  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement stage:\n- Introducing illegal funds into financial system\n- Converting cash to other financial instruments\n\n2. Layering stage:\n- Creating complex financial transactions\n- Obscuring original source of funds\n- Separating money from illegal origin\n\n3. Integration stage:\n- Reintroducing funds into legitimate economy\n- Making illegal funds appear legal\n\nCommon legal definitions across jurisdictions include:\n- Concealing criminal proceeds\n- Disguising source of illegal funds\n- Transferring assets obtained through criminal activity\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legitimate\n\nMost jurisdictions criminalize money laundering under specific statutes, with penalties including:\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nSpecific definitions can vary between countries, but generally involve intentional efforts to hide the origins of criminally derived funds.\n\nWould you like me to provide more technical or jurisdictional details about money laundering definitions?",
